            <input type="number" id="accountNumber" name="accountNumber" required
                title="Enter your Account number"><br><br>

            <label>IFSC</label>
            <input type="text" id="ifsc" name="ifsc" pattern="[A-Z]{4}0[0-9A-Z]{6}" placeholder="HDFC0001234" required
                title="Enter your IFSC"><br><br>
        </fieldset>

        <!--Declarqations-->
        <fieldset>
            <legend>
                <h1><b><i>Declarations</i></b></h1>
            </legend>


            <input type="checkbox" id="declare" name="declare" required>
            <label for="declare">I here by declare that the Information is accurate </label>
        </fieldset>



        <button type="submit">Submit Form</button>
        <button type="reset">Reset Form</button>

    </form>
</body>

</html>

------------------------------------------------Tables -------------------------------------------------

# HTML Tables - Complete Guide

## Importance of Tables

**Real-time Definition:** Tables are used to display data in a structured, row-and-column format. In real-world applications, they organize information systematically for easy reading and comparison.

**Real-time Use Cases:**
- Employee databases and directories
- Product catalogs with prices
- Student grade reports
- Financial statements and reports
- Inventory management systems
- Timetables and schedules
- Comparison charts

---

## Basic Table Structure


